<br>
One death came in quite amusing circumstances when Taallon cam over to meet me and hand me a wonderful new robe...we decided to have some fun with the wandering turkeys and played a few games of nuke-tennis before Taallon accidentally snared himself and almost died to one particularly large chicken...he just managed to invis in time but unfortunately this nasty piece of poultry soon did for me. Taallon took it to heart (although he had no reason to) it was simply too funny to take seriously.<br>
<br>
Later I wandered over to meet friends in FM and bumped into Ztransporter, fresh with her new level 29 spells <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   but soon she found herself (quite accidentally) with both a giant and some overblown hedgehog on her heels. I did my best to distract the giant who was closest to her, but unluckily all I managed to do was secure the attentions of the spiney-backed monster onto myself...it's first spell cast on me hit me for 208...and my sow had gone. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Z was kind enough to drag my corpse to zone when I heard from Llainya, sorry to hear of my misfortunes. By this point I was much deeper back into 33 of course and just about giving up hope of 34 spells when Llainya found a Vicar friend willing to camp the Mage he was playing and relog on to rez me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
A great kindness this was, at 4am his local time, and I am very grateful to him. <br>
<br>
I would like to ask the assistance of the guild to repay this kind gentleman who I requries Words of Concordance for his Mage - if you have any I can buy, or loot any you can spare please send me a tell so that I can go some way towards repaying the debt I owe this fine man.<br>
<br>
Gladriel Lumenaura <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/ugladriellumenaura.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gladriel Lumenaura</A> at: 7/1/01 6:32:30 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uordained.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ordained</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#8B4513>(7/1/01 12:29:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balthazer</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I am good friend with this cleric, little dorf guy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  He and I go WAY back in EQ. I am sure I can find the words for his 57 .. or was it 58? Magician.. hehe..I will send him tells buggin him about it later...Grat job in OT, btw =)<br>
